                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d661">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">741.61/903: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-25T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 25, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>691. Your 1390, October 22, 5 p.m.,<note n="36" xml:id="d661fn36">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_667">p. 667</ref>.</note> and
                    1393, October 23, 4 p.m. For your strictly confidential information, this
                    Government does not <pb facs="0635" n="623" xml:id="pg_623"/> share the view
                    that an agreement, if reached, between Japan and the Soviet Union at this time
                    would “probably bring about a collapse of Chinese resistance.” You may in your
                    discretion so inform your British colleague.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
